WHAT IS AGPL-3.0?
==================

The GNU Affero General Public License is a free, copyleft license for software and other kinds of works,
specifically designed to ensure cooperation with the community in the case of network server software.

KEY REQUIREMENTS
================

If you use, modify, or distribute this software, you MUST:

1. **Preserve Attribution**:
   - Include the text: "Based on Thoughts & Time by Sawt Dakhili"
   - Provide a link to the original project: https://github.com/sawtdakhili/Thoughts-Time
   - Retain all copyright notices

2. **Share Source Code**:
   - If you modify this software and run it as a network service (web app, API, etc.)
   - You MUST provide the complete source code to users who interact with it
   - The source code must be easily accessible (e.g., GitHub repo link in the UI)

3. **Use Same License**:
   - Any derivative works must be licensed under AGPL-3.0
   - You cannot relicense under a more restrictive or permissive license

4. **Indicate Changes**:
   - Clearly state what modifications you have made
   - Include a changelog or modified files list

NETWORK USE = DISTRIBUTION
===========================

The key feature of AGPL-3.0 is the "network use" clause:

If you run a modified version of this software on a server and let others interact with it
over a network (like a web application), you must provide them with access to the source code.

This prevents proprietary cloud services from taking the code without contributing back.

RECOMMENDED ATTRIBUTION FORMAT
===============================

**For source code:**
```
// Based on Thoughts & Time by Sawt Dakhili
// https://github.com/sawtdakhili/Thoughts-Time
// Licensed under AGPL-3.0
// Modified: [describe your changes]
```

**For web applications (add to footer/about page):**
```
Powered by Thoughts & Time by Sawt Dakhili
https://github.com/sawtdakhili/Thoughts-Time
Licensed under AGPL-3.0 | View Source Code
```

**For documentation/README:**
```
This project is based on [Thoughts & Time](https://github.com/sawtdakhili/Thoughts-Time)
by Sawt Dakhili, licensed under [AGPL-3.0](https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.html).

Changes made: [describe your modifications]
```

COMMERCIAL USE
==============

✅ YES, you can use this software commercially!

AGPL-3.0 allows commercial use, but requires:
- Providing source code to network users
- Licensing modifications under AGPL-3.0
- Maintaining attribution

This means:
- You can charge for hosting services ✅
- You can sell support/consulting ✅
- You can run it for your business ✅
- BUT: You must share your modifications if users interact with them over a network

